						<paratext>
							<cite.query w-src-number="0287017168" w-serial-number="1981100885" w-seq-number="00020" w-ref-type="RP" w-pub-number="0000711" ID="Ife1318c274d211eab2f0b920da2605c5">A. S. Wikstrom, Inc. v. Norair Engineering Corp., 156 Ga. App. 49, 274 S.E.2d 28 (1980)</cite.query>, held that an affidavit of a party on a motion for summary judgment could be introduced for impeachment, but it is not an admission in judicio, and the party may testify to the contrary.<eos/>
